div.p:
Lettice ſown in Auguſt, will live all Winter;
but if they are ſown in March, they will be ſo
bitter, that they cannot be eaten.

Crocaſſes muſt be uſed and ſet as the Tulip;
if the Gardiner ſet them in his Borders, they
will make a pretty ſhew in the Spring.

Dutch-box grows green moſt part of the
year, it is very handſom for Works and Borders;
he may part the Roots and ſet them.
